## Priority Guidelines

| Priority | Definition | Examples |
|----------|------------|----------|
| P0 | Critical - Must have for launch | Core functionality, security, basic user flow |
| P1 | High - Needed for good experience | Enhanced features, performance, major platforms |
| P2 | Medium - Nice to have | Customization, advanced features, edge cases |
| P3 | Low - Future consideration | Ecosystem integrations, power user features |

